00:22:29,070 --> 00:22:29,870
Okay.

567
00:22:30,470 --> 00:22:31,350
I'll get a new watch then.

568
00:22:31,350 --> 00:22:33,340
But we don't need to buy a new phone for your dad.

569
00:22:33,340 --> 00:22:34,180
He doesn't have much business to do.

570
00:22:34,180 --> 00:22:35,270
He doesn't need it.

571
00:22:35,270 --> 00:22:36,950
No, we must get him a new one.

572
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:38,710
Later, when my dad gets a new phone

573
00:22:38,710 --> 00:22:40,770
and shows it off in front of Uncle Xie.

574
00:22:40,880 --> 00:22:42,150
"Look, look."

575
00:22:42,630 --> 00:22:44,490
"My daughter bought this for me."

576
00:22:44,520 --> 00:22:47,300
"Let your son buy you a new cell phone someday, huh?"

577
00:22:47,300 --> 00:22:49,640
Then Wanghe will get another beating.

578
00:22:50,800 --> 00:22:52,480
You bad girl.

579
00:22:54,030 --> 00:22:54,960
Remember.

580
00:22:55,780 --> 00:22:57,120
In the future, for any matter,

581
00:22:57,120 --> 00:22:59,450
always discuss it with your family first.

582
00:22:59,540 --> 00:23:01,800
I'm afraid you'll be taken advantage of.

583
00:23:02,720 --> 00:23:03,600
Did you hear me?

584
00:23:03,920 --> 00:23:05,440
I'm being serious here.

585
00:23:09,290 --> 00:23:11,200
Your dad is here to support the family.

586
00:23:11,200 --> 00:23:12,730
We don't need you to do that.

587
00:23:13,880 --> 00:23:15,220
I know, I know.

588
00:23:26,470 --> 00:23:27,030
Boss.

589
00:23:28,130 --> 00:23:28,860
Come on.

590
00:23:30,650 --> 00:23:32,140
Are you out of your mind?

591
00:23:33,290 --> 00:23:34,070
Your liver doesn't hurt anymore?

592
00:23:34,070 --> 00:23:36,510
Not afraid of your wife scolding you anymore?

593
00:23:36,510 --> 00:23:38,050
Let her scold me if she wants.

594
00:23:38,050 --> 00:23:39,660
Well, let's drink first.

595
00:23:39,700 --> 00:23:40,630
Come on, come on.

596
00:23:41,770 --> 00:23:43,970
The heck with it. I'm already like this.

597
00:23:54,010 --> 00:23:55,470
Have you lost your spirit?

598
00:23:57,030 --> 00:23:58,440
It's just the beginning.

599
00:24:00,370 --> 00:24:01,770
All of these setbacks...

600
00:24:02,490 --> 00:24:04,270
are all temporary.

601
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:11,500
It's okay if we just can't

602
00:24:12,060 --> 00:24:13,200
get the money back.

603
00:24:14,340 --> 00:24:16,070
We can always earn more, right?

604
00:24:16,960 --> 00:24:19,430
These days, I keep feeling that... the...

605
00:24:21,990 --> 00:24:23,200
the Grand Canal...

606
00:24:25,770 --> 00:24:26,660
is finished.

607
00:24:29,190 --> 00:24:30,190
Have you noticed?

608
00:24:30,190 --> 00:24:31,150
These days,

609
00:24:31,510 --> 00:24:34,950
there are fewer and fewer ships on the river,

610
00:24:35,240 --> 00:24:36,630
while the cars on the highway

611
00:24:36,630 --> 00:24:38,390
are increasing day by day.

612
00:24:40,710 --> 00:24:41,950
I'm getting...

613
00:24:43,080 --> 00:24:44,260
really anxious.

614
00:24:44,260 --> 00:24:46,350
I'm in a complete panic.

615
00:24:52,330 --> 00:24:53,460
Let me tell you.

616
00:24:54,630 --> 00:24:57,080
This is all... all temporary.

617
00:24:57,520 --> 00:24:58,600
It will pass.

618
00:25:00,020 --> 00:25:00,670
Right?

619
00:25:01,090 --> 00:25:02,650
Mr. Zhou said

620
00:25:02,770 --> 00:25:04,070
that this Grand Canal

621
00:25:04,070 --> 00:25:07,490
was dug since the Spring and Autumn period.

622
00:25:08,540 --> 00:25:10,790
It took over two thousand years to complete it.

623
00:25:10,790 --> 00:25:12,110
It's witnessed so many dynasties

624
00:25:12,110 --> 00:25:14,070
and supported so many people.

625
00:25:15,700 --> 00:25:17,690
As long as we don't give up on it,

626
00:25:18,480 --> 00:25:19,720
I firmly believe

627
00:25:19,760 --> 00:25:22,090
that this canal will also not give up on us.

628
00:25:22,680 --> 00:25:24,510
I hope it's like that too.

629
00:25:24,760 --> 00:25:25,810
Right?

630
00:25:26,590 --> 00:25:29,520
You know, I've been following you since we were kids.

631
00:25:29,990 --> 00:25:33,880
Well, whatever we do, you've always called the shots.

632
00:25:34,080 --> 00:25:36,070
You make all the big decisions and major ideas,

633
00:25:36,070 --> 00:25:37,600
and I just follow your lead.

634
00:25:37,910 --> 00:25:39,770
I'll do whatever you say.

635
00:25:40,440 --> 00:25:41,120
But...

636
00:25:44,390 --> 00:25:46,570
but now I'm really starting to feel...

637
00:25:47,230 --> 00:25:49,290
feel like I can't hold on much longer.

638
00:25:54,510 --> 00:25:56,990
Just think about how many days we've fallen behind

639
00:25:56,990 --> 00:25:59,520
on paying the dividends we owe to each family.

640
00:26:00,830 --> 00:26:02,510
We all live in the same compound,

641
00:26:02,510 --> 00:26:04,750
seeing each other every day.

642
00:26:08,890 --> 00:26:11,620
My family's living expenses are about to run out.

643
00:26:15,530 --> 00:26:18,530
Next year, Fenghua will be taking the college entrance exam.

644
00:26:18,530 --> 00:26:20,610
If she doesn't get in, that's fine.

645
00:26:21,120 --> 00:26:23,290
But what if she does?

646
00:26:24,070 --> 00:26:27,070
Where will I get the money for her tuition, Tiancheng?

647
00:26:28,790 --> 00:26:30,550
You also want to sell the ship?

648
00:26:39,460 --> 00:26:40,130
But...

649
00:26:40,150 --> 00:26:43,030
we bought this ship to make money, right?

650
00:26:44,470 --> 00:26:46,580
Not for sentimental reasons, right?

651
00:26:46,610 --> 00:26:48,320
But if we don't do seafaring,

652
00:26:48,350 --> 00:26:49,610
what are we going to do?

653
00:26:52,000 --> 00:26:52,840
Tiancheng,

654
00:26:53,620 --> 00:26:54,700
look...

655
00:26:54,940 --> 00:26:57,080
your destiny is tied to the water.

656
00:26:57,120 --> 00:26:59,820
Can't we find a place by the river...

657
00:27:00,400 --> 00:27:02,450
and do some fish farming or something?

658
00:27:02,450 --> 00:27:04,440
My brother-in-law knows an expert from Shanghai.

659
00:27:04,440 --> 00:27:05,400
He said

660
00:27:05,420 --> 00:27:07,830
that raising eels or turtles can make money.

661
00:27:07,830 --> 00:27:08,410
At the very least,

662
00:27:08,410 --> 00:27:09,940
we could set up a fish pond

663
00:27:10,540 --> 00:27:11,820
and start a farmstay.

664
00:27:11,900 --> 00:27:13,180
That's still better than this

665
00:27:13,180 --> 00:27:15,240
half-dead state we're in now, right?

666
00:27:34,560 --> 00:27:35,440
Mom.

667
00:27:36,030 --> 00:27:38,540
Your waist hasn't recovered yet. Why are you running?

668
00:27:38,540 --> 00:27:40,000
See? You're in pain again.

669
00:27:49,140 --> 00:27:51,510
You need to wear this back brace even when you sleep at night.

670
00:27:51,510 --> 00:27:53,730
Won't that give me a rash around my waist?

671
00:27:53,730 --> 00:27:56,070
That's still better than a sore back, isn't it?

672
00:27:56,070 --> 00:27:57,240
The doctor said...

673
00:27:58,250 --> 00:27:59,260
that if you don't rest,

674
00:27:59,260 --> 00:28:01,660
your waist will be easily affected by the cold.

675
00:28:01,660 --> 00:28:03,630
Stop worrying about me.

676
00:28:03,810 --> 00:28:05,140
If you have this much spare time,

677
00:28:05,140 --> 00:28:06,900
go hit the books.

678
00:28:09,960 --> 00:28:11,290
Are you feeling better?

679
00:28:12,680 --> 00:28:13,740
Much better.

680
00:28:16,240 --> 00:28:17,590
It's just that I can't do

681
00:28:17,620 --> 00:28:19,320
any heavy work for a while.

682
00:28:19,590 --> 00:28:21,190
I'll need to rest for a while.

683
00:28:21,300 --> 00:28:22,300
Come and eat.

684
00:28:22,580 --> 00:28:23,300
Alright.

685
00:28:23,320 --> 00:28:24,590
Then you should rest.

686
00:28:24,750 --> 00:28:26,050
Take it as a break.

687
00:28:26,620 --> 00:28:29,750
There's not much business on the streets lately anyway.

688
00:28:30,500 --> 00:28:31,750
You drink first.

689
00:28:31,750 --> 00:28:33,410
There are more dishes coming.

690
00:28:52,330 --> 00:28:54,390
How much money do we have left at home?

691
00:28:55,730 --> 00:28:57,060
Not much.

692
00:29:01,990 --> 00:29:03,360
Why do you ask?

693
00:29:04,250 --> 00:29:05,990
Didn't Chen Bo publish a book?

694
00:29:08,150 --> 00:29:10,280
So, I'm planning to self-publish one.

695
00:29:10,710 --> 00:29:11,570
Self-publish?

696
00:29:14,400 --> 00:29:16,220
I was just thinking...

697
00:29:16,710 --> 00:29:17,890
you see...

698
00:29:18,450 --> 00:29:21,090
our son will be going to college next year, right?

699
00:29:21,090 --> 00:29:23,150
Shouldn't we save more money for him?

700
00:29:32,830 --> 00:29:33,710
Forget it.

701
00:29:36,550 --> 00:29:38,750
I'll go chase Boss Xie for our dividend.

702
00:29:40,460 --> 00:29:42,010
No, no, no.

703
00:29:42,540 --> 00:29:45,180
If he hasn't given it, it means he's in a tough spot.

704
00:29:45,180 --> 00:29:46,150
If he is earning money,

705
00:29:46,150 --> 00:29:47,470
hasn't he already given us?

706
00:29:47,470 --> 00:29:47,790
Don't go.

707
00:29:47,790 --> 00:29:50,190
No, but he can't always be in a tight spot.

708
00:29:50,680 --> 00:29:52,520
How long has he owed us now?

709
00:29:53,210 --> 00:29:55,810
If he really had no business, I wouldn't say anything.

710
00:29:55,810 --> 00:29:56,910
But Boss Xie,

711
00:29:57,270 --> 00:29:58,750
he's shipping trip by trip.

712
00:29:58,750 --> 00:30:00,150
If he's not making money,

713
00:30:00,150 --> 00:30:01,330
why is he bothering with all of this?

714
00:30:01,330 --> 00:30:03,100
He might as well sell the ship.

715
00:30:03,430 --> 00:30:04,160
Listen to me.

716
00:30:04,160 --> 00:30:05,600
I've thought it through.

717
00:30:05,630 --> 00:30:06,430
I'll learn embroidery.

718
00:30:06,430 --> 00:30:07,940
Once I get the hang of it, I can earn money.

719
00:30:07,940 --> 00:30:09,490
How long will that take?

720
00:30:09,510 --> 00:30:10,570
I've asked around.

721
00:30:10,590 --> 00:30:12,090
There's a big demand in the market.

722
00:30:12,090 --> 00:30:13,150
As long as the quality is good,

723
00:30:13,150 --> 00:30:14,030
we won't have to worry about selling.

724
00:30:14,030 --> 00:30:15,910
I need cash now!

725
00:30:15,950 --> 00:30:18,390
Besides, it's Xie who owes us!

726
00:30:18,470 --> 00:30:20,790
Since when did the debtors get to call the shots?

727
00:30:20,790 --> 00:30:22,120
It's ridiculous, isn't it?

728
00:30:22,120 --> 00:30:22,640
You...

729
00:30:25,430 --> 00:30:26,110
Come...

730
00:30:26,740 --> 00:30:27,510
Mom.

731
00:30:28,160 --> 00:30:30,020
You've strained your back again?

732
00:30:30,790 --> 00:30:32,240
Go sit down, quick.

733
00:30:32,550 --> 00:30:33,310
Easy, easy.

734
00:30:41,620 --> 00:30:43,590
Pay attention. What's on your mind?

735
00:30:43,590 --> 00:30:45,390
You're spilling it everywhere.

736
00:30:46,220 --> 00:30:47,930
What are you thinking about?

737
00:30:48,200 --> 00:30:50,020
About Fenghua's contract,

738
00:30:50,060 --> 00:30:53,190
the more I think about it, the more it doesn't feel right.

739
00:30:53,350 --> 00:30:54,680
Why does it not feel right?

740
00:30:54,680 --> 00:30:57,800
If Siyi signed a contract to be a model, I'd believe it.

741
00:30:57,980 --> 00:30:59,020
Fenghua...

742
00:30:59,040 --> 00:31:00,580
What about her?

743
00:31:00,620 --> 00:31:03,060
Are you saying Fenghua isn't beautiful?

744
00:31:03,150 --> 00:31:03,950
She's frumpy.

745
00:31:05,270 --> 00:31:06,870
As if you're so fashionable.

746
00:31:06,920 --> 00:31:08,690
Then why didn't they sign you?

747
00:31:08,720 --> 00:31:10,580
I don't make a living off my looks.

748
00:31:10,920 --> 00:31:12,780
Then what do you make a living off?

749
00:31:12,780 --> 00:31:13,740
Your ability?

750
00:31:15,260 --> 00:31:16,020
Haihong.

751
00:31:16,330 --> 00:31:17,320
Uncle Shao.

752
00:31:17,340 --> 00:31:18,090
Wanghe,

753
00:31:18,350 --> 00:31:19,380
is your dad home?

754
00:31:19,480 --> 00:31:20,110
He's not.

755
00:31:20,150 --> 00:31:22,020
Do you need to see him for something?

756
00:31:22,020 --> 00:31:23,260
No, no, no.

757
00:31:24,980 --> 00:31:26,130
Mr. Shao.

758
00:31:29,860 --> 00:31:33,080
I'll have our Xie find you when he gets back.

759
00:31:33,790 --> 00:31:34,900
Okay.

760
00:31:35,750 --> 00:31:37,110
I'll be off then.

761
00:31:51,620 --> 00:31:52,680
What's the matter?

762
00:31:54,580 --> 00:31:56,070
He came for his dividends.

763
00:31:58,270 --> 00:32:00,050
We can't really blame him.

764
00:32:00,190 --> 00:32:01,070
This time...

765
00:32:02,150 --> 00:32:04,680
it's really been dragged out for far too long.

766
00:32:04,710 --> 00:32:05,960
If I were your father,

767
00:32:06,390 --> 00:32:08,390
I'd be too embarrassed to come home.

768
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:18,160
Don't always be at odds with Yan.

769
00:32:18,190 --> 00:32:19,250
Alright, alright.

770
00:32:21,020 --> 00:32:21,950
Right?

771
00:32:21,950 --> 00:32:22,430
Yes, yes.

772
00:32:22,430 --> 00:32:23,200
Boss.

773
00:32:24,190 --> 00:32:25,170
Mr. Shao.

774
00:32:26,220 --> 00:32:27,350
My dad is back.

775
00:32:27,480 --> 00:32:28,200
Well...

776
00:32:28,650 --> 00:32:29,750
Light-headed.

777
00:32:30,220 --> 00:32:30,860
Boss?

778
00:32:35,770 --> 00:32:36,740
Well...

779
00:32:36,960 --> 00:32:37,760
Lao'er?

780
00:32:38,270 --> 00:32:40,470
You go back first.

781
00:32:40,510 --> 00:32:42,270
We... we'll chat for a bit.

782
00:32:50,270 --> 00:32:51,800
Please... please go ahead.

783
00:32:56,190 --> 00:32:57,150
It's...

784
00:32:57,550 --> 00:32:59,110
about the dividends.

785
00:33:00,190 --> 00:33:02,670
I'm a bit tight on cash recently,

786
00:33:02,670 --> 00:33:04,150
and I urgently need it.

787
00:33:04,790 --> 00:33:07,720
Otherwise, I wouldn't have brought this up with you.

788
00:33:07,780 --> 00:33:08,630
I understand.

789
00:33:09,190 --> 00:33:10,790
I understand. I understand.

790
00:33:11,790 --> 00:33:14,320
Give me one more week.

791
00:33:14,750 --> 00:33:17,770
I'll definitely... resolve this issue.

792
00:33:19,030 --> 00:33:19,950
One week?

793
00:33:21,300 --> 00:33:22,110
You...

794
00:33:22,510 --> 00:33:25,510
you're... in such a hurry... for money?

795
00:33:26,710 --> 00:33:28,110
It's not that.

796
00:33:28,850 --> 00:33:30,490
I heard

797
00:33:30,520 --> 00:33:33,060
that Crippled Sun even sold his own car

798
00:33:33,140 --> 00:33:34,740
and then ran off.

799
00:33:35,760 --> 00:33:37,490
I'm afraid you'll get scammed.

800
00:33:46,080 --> 00:33:48,030
Then, can you still get back the money

801
00:33:48,030 --> 00:33:49,520
he owes you?

802
00:33:54,210 --> 00:33:55,350
I...

803
00:33:57,560 --> 00:33:59,200
Be careful, be careful.

804
00:33:59,360 --> 00:34:00,960
I... I...

805
00:34:01,790 --> 00:34:03,840
I'll do my best to get it back.

806
00:34:06,030 --> 00:34:07,270
If not,

807
00:34:07,540 --> 00:34:09,630
I still have a backup plan.

808
00:34:09,650 --> 00:34:11,870
You've finally decided to sell the ship?

809
00:34:11,870 --> 00:34:13,159
I've said this before.

810
00:34:13,190 --> 00:34:14,989
The canal business is finished.

811
00:34:15,070 --> 00:34:16,610
If we don't cut our losses now,

812
00:34:16,610 --> 00:34:18,810
we may really end up losing everything.

813
00:34:20,190 --> 00:34:21,870
Are you all...

814
00:34:22,719 --> 00:34:24,719
just waiting for me to sell the ship?

815
00:34:26,590 --> 00:34:28,020
It's just a suggestion.

816
00:34:28,710 --> 00:34:29,989
Whether you take it or not

817
00:34:29,989 --> 00:34:30,960
is up to you.

818
00:34:32,010 --> 00:34:33,489
But I think,

819
00:34:34,190 --> 00:34:36,389
now that we're in a market economy, after all,

820
00:34:36,389 --> 00:34:40,350
doing business still needs to follow market principles.

821
00:34:40,469 --> 00:34:42,199
We can't do things recklessly.

822
00:34:43,110 --> 00:34:44,280
What do you think?

823
00:34:46,750 --> 00:34:47,550
Right.

824
00:34:48,750 --> 00:34:51,190
What you say... makes sense.

825
00:34:52,010 --> 00:34:52,770
Makes sense.

826
00:34:59,070 --> 00:35:01,310
Wanghe has reviewed the contract.

827
00:35:01,440 --> 00:35:03,370
He said there's no problem with it.

828
00:35:08,270 --> 00:35:09,610
Does shooting commercials

829
00:35:09,610 --> 00:35:10,810
really pay that much?

830
00:35:11,290 --> 00:35:13,740
Still, not just anyone can make money from it.

831
00:35:13,740 --> 00:35:16,140
It means our daughter has good conditions.

832
00:35:16,190 --> 00:35:17,940
They came to us.

833
00:35:18,310 --> 00:35:21,440
If it were someone else, they wouldn't even come to them.

834
00:35:30,090 --> 00:35:32,630
If she can make money from it, let her do it first.

835
00:35:32,630 --> 00:35:34,630
Let her earn the tuition fees first.

836
00:35:35,550 --> 00:35:36,830
With her brain,

837
00:35:36,870 --> 00:35:39,670
though, I'm not sure she'll even get into college.

838
00:35:39,750 --> 00:35:40,550
However,

839
00:35:40,950 --> 00:35:42,230
I think modeling is just a career

840
00:35:42,230 --> 00:35:43,810
that expires with youth.

841
00:35:43,990 --> 00:35:45,520
While she's still young,

842
00:35:45,630 --> 00:35:47,390
she can earn as much as possible.

843
00:35:47,390 --> 00:35:48,990
Once she has enough saved up,

844
00:35:48,990 --> 00:35:50,390
we can open a restaurant.

845
00:35:50,400 --> 00:35:51,670
What restaurant?

846
00:35:53,480 --> 00:35:55,610
With the current economic situation,

